WEBVTT

00:01.735 --> 00:03.037
Your suffering's over now.

00:03.071 --> 00:04.338
[ Television playing
in background ]

00:04.372 --> 00:06.240
Mine's just about to begin.

00:08.008 --> 00:09.377
Say something!

00:09.410 --> 00:12.846
It's happening! The
most heralded of DiMeo
holiday traditions.

00:12.880 --> 00:13.947
Ha ha!
[ Television turns off ]

00:13.981 --> 00:15.516
Macy's parade?
Football?

00:15.549 --> 00:18.252
No, Mom trying to get out
of doing Thanksgiving.

00:18.286 --> 00:20.554
Okay, don't let her win,
but she works hard.

00:20.588 --> 00:21.722
Let's give her
some false hope.

00:21.755 --> 00:24.225
First --
the fun alternative.

00:24.258 --> 00:25.693
Hey, guys!

00:25.726 --> 00:28.196
Crazy idea for Thanksgiving --
Disneyland.

00:28.229 --> 00:29.763
Right? Right?

00:29.797 --> 00:31.899
Give thanks for short lines
on "Pirates."

00:31.932 --> 00:34.568
Aww,
but my class just went.

00:34.602 --> 00:36.270
What? Well, that's it.
No more school for you.

00:36.304 --> 00:37.838
[ Quietly ]
Now the moral high ground.

00:37.871 --> 00:40.408
Are we sure that we want to
celebrate this holiday at all?

00:40.441 --> 00:42.610
Because the historical
implications are --

00:42.643 --> 00:43.877
I'd posit the roots
of the tradition go back

00:43.911 --> 00:46.447
to the harvest festivals
of the Babylonian celebrations

00:46.480 --> 00:47.481
of the Great Mother.

00:47.515 --> 00:48.749
Oh, would you posit that?
Would you?

00:48.782 --> 00:51.119
Vaguely worded
emotional instability.

00:51.152 --> 00:52.720
[ Voice breaking ]
You guys, I'm just --

00:52.753 --> 00:54.455
I'm going through some stuff
right now.

00:54.488 --> 00:55.756
Chinese buffet.

00:55.789 --> 00:57.258
What if we went
to the Chinese buffet?

00:57.291 --> 00:59.160
Fun.
JJ, what do you think?

00:59.193 --> 01:01.562
"It is my favorite holiday.

01:01.595 --> 01:04.832
You know, I am going to college
next year.

01:04.865 --> 01:08.236
Will I have a tradition
to come home for?"

01:08.269 --> 01:10.371
You suck.

01:10.404 --> 01:13.541
"You know,
the Italians have a saying,

01:13.574 --> 01:15.943
'A tavola, non s'invecchia.'

01:15.976 --> 01:19.480
At the table --"
I said I'd bloody do it,
Kenneth! Shut it!

01:19.513 --> 01:22.450
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:22.483 --> 01:24.452
**

01:24.485 --> 01:26.354
I just don't get the premise

01:26.387 --> 01:28.021
of the holiday.

01:28.055 --> 01:30.558
What happened between the
pilgrims and the Indians was t--

01:30.591 --> 01:32.326
It's over, Mom.
Take the "L."

01:32.360 --> 01:34.562
Mom, Dad, I'm ready.

01:34.595 --> 01:35.596
Cool.

01:35.629 --> 01:37.531
For what, you might ask?

01:37.565 --> 01:38.999
To get back with Taylor.

01:39.032 --> 01:41.101
I've been waiting for a sign
that I'd matured enough,

01:41.135 --> 01:44.672
and this morning,
I awoke with a chest hair.

01:44.705 --> 01:47.040
What do you think,
little buddy?

01:47.074 --> 01:48.776
He winked.
It's on.

01:48.809 --> 01:51.078
I don't know, guys.
We dropped him a couple times.

01:51.111 --> 01:52.180
Maybe that's it.

01:53.647 --> 01:55.316
Dylan: Hey, Mom.
Uncle Billy just pulled up.

01:55.349 --> 01:57.885
[ Horn honking ]
It looks so nice in there.

01:57.918 --> 01:59.720
Would you mind
if I joined you?

01:59.753 --> 02:01.422
And...none of that.

02:01.455 --> 02:02.556
[ Oven door creaks ]

02:02.590 --> 02:04.592
Every year,
I look for the worst in Billy...

02:04.625 --> 02:06.527
[ Doorbell rings ]
...and I find it.

02:06.560 --> 02:07.961
This year,
I'm looking for the good.

02:07.995 --> 02:09.330
I mean, we --

02:09.363 --> 02:11.265
we used to have fun
when we were young.

02:11.299 --> 02:12.633
We can have fun again.

02:12.666 --> 02:13.934
You're not
getting divorced.

02:13.967 --> 02:15.936
Stop being dramatic
and go answer the door.

02:15.969 --> 02:18.138
[ Doorbell rings ]

02:18.172 --> 02:21.375
[ Doorbell ringing rapidly ]

02:21.409 --> 02:22.343
[ Inhales deeply ]

02:22.376 --> 02:23.644
[ Ringing continues ]

02:23.677 --> 02:26.347
Hey!
[ Laughs ]

02:26.380 --> 02:28.182
Billy,
good to see you.

02:28.216 --> 02:29.650
-Yeah.
-You look great.

02:29.683 --> 02:31.752
Don't I?
Yeah, the chick I'm dating

02:31.785 --> 02:33.254
just got me
to go vegan.

02:33.287 --> 02:35.956
I mean, you guys can eat meat
if you have to, I guess,

02:35.989 --> 02:37.825
but can you have Crabby Spice
whip me up

02:37.858 --> 02:39.493
something cruelty-free?

02:40.461 --> 02:43.030
So, you're seeing someone!

02:43.063 --> 02:44.164
Is it the lawyer
you told me about?

02:44.198 --> 02:45.699
Yeah, kinda.
It's her daughter.

02:45.733 --> 02:47.835
You know, like, [high-pitched]
"You should meet my kid.

02:47.868 --> 02:49.069
She's great."

02:49.102 --> 02:50.103
[ Normal voice ] Well,
I'll tell you what --

02:50.137 --> 02:51.639
Granny wasn't lying.

02:51.672 --> 02:53.341
Mm.
[ Laughs ]

02:53.374 --> 02:54.475
You get it.
I'm young!

02:54.508 --> 02:56.444
I shouldn't be dating
someone old enough

02:56.477 --> 02:58.279
to take heart medicine.

02:58.312 --> 03:01.415
Oh, that reminds me. I-I gotta
take my heart medicine.

03:01.449 --> 03:03.016
Hey, hon!

03:03.050 --> 03:05.486
I found that thing I said
was gonna be fun!

03:05.519 --> 03:06.654
It's not!

03:06.687 --> 03:10.658
Hey! Happy Thanksgiving,
DiMeos!

03:10.691 --> 03:11.859
Who's this --
JJ's new guy?

03:11.892 --> 03:13.927
What happened to the
good-looking one from last year?

03:14.962 --> 03:16.264
Nice to meet you.

03:16.297 --> 03:18.566
**

03:18.599 --> 03:19.833
[ Cellphone beeping ]

03:19.867 --> 03:21.569
JJ!

03:21.602 --> 03:22.803
Medicine time!

03:22.836 --> 03:24.238
Oh, come on!
You don't have to do that.

03:24.272 --> 03:25.739
You're a guest today.

03:25.773 --> 03:27.275
Nah, Jimmy.
I got this.

03:27.308 --> 03:28.642
Hey.

03:29.877 --> 03:31.345
Hey, what's the new guy
doing with my heart pills?

03:31.379 --> 03:34.448
**

03:34.482 --> 03:37.618
-Okay, grab JJ's bag.
-Got it.

03:37.651 --> 03:38.852
You bring the pills.

03:38.886 --> 03:40.821
Got 'em.
Come on. Hurry up.

03:40.854 --> 03:43.190
I'm sorry.
I-I wasn't paying attention.

03:43.223 --> 03:45.359
Not making it better, new guy.
Let's go. Go.

03:45.393 --> 03:47.295
You're gonna be fine,
but we'll need to keep him

03:47.328 --> 03:48.329
overnight for observation.

03:48.362 --> 03:49.430
We're gonna get him
a room.

03:49.463 --> 03:50.564
Okay, thank you.

03:50.598 --> 03:53.534
"Another JJ hospital visit
ruins everything."

03:53.567 --> 03:55.102
What has a hospital visit
ever ruined?

03:55.135 --> 03:57.538
"Vacations,
graduations,

03:57.571 --> 03:59.106
Dad's perfect
bowling game."

03:59.139 --> 04:01.909
Oh, come on.
He rolled one strike.

04:01.942 --> 04:04.512
The alley was playing
all of Tom Petty's
"Full Moon Fever."

04:04.545 --> 04:05.746
I was not going to miss.

04:05.779 --> 04:06.580
Dude, you're killing me.

04:06.614 --> 04:07.915
Nothing's ruined.

04:07.948 --> 04:09.249
What's more, I'm gonna
figure out a way

04:09.283 --> 04:11.251
of making this
the best Thanksgiving ever.

04:11.285 --> 04:13.421
Who's with me?

04:13.454 --> 04:15.255
Really all depends
on the plan.

04:15.289 --> 04:18.826
Well, I don't have it yet,
but just imagine it's great.

04:18.859 --> 04:20.428
Huh.
Sounds pretty good.

04:20.461 --> 04:22.095
-Yeah, not bad.
-That should work.

04:22.129 --> 04:23.797
There you go.
How hard was that?

04:23.831 --> 04:27.868
Hey. They're gonna keep him
for observation, but he's fine.

04:27.901 --> 04:30.103
Jimmy, I-I can't believe
this happened.

04:30.137 --> 04:32.573
I-If there's anything --
anything I can do --

04:32.606 --> 04:34.241
Yeah, you can
make out somewhere

04:34.274 --> 04:35.876
that isn't blocking
the dang game.

04:35.909 --> 04:37.878
Hey, Billy.
Comfortable?

04:37.911 --> 04:39.647
God, no.
I hate hospitals.

04:39.680 --> 04:41.815
Aww, see, lucky for us,
we have a kid with disabilities

04:41.849 --> 04:43.384
since we love hospitals.

04:43.417 --> 04:44.752
Hey. The kid's
gonna be okay, right?

04:44.785 --> 04:46.454
-Well --
-Oh!

04:46.487 --> 04:47.588
That's not roughing
the passer!

04:47.621 --> 04:49.590
Come on!

04:49.623 --> 04:50.758
Hey, you want to help?

04:50.791 --> 04:52.059
Deal with him.

04:52.092 --> 04:53.494
I can't handle
the "Billy Show" today.

04:53.527 --> 04:55.696
Uh...Oh-ho.

04:55.729 --> 04:56.764
Mm...

04:56.797 --> 04:57.798
Mm...

04:57.831 --> 04:58.999
Rrrrr....

04:59.032 --> 05:00.233
How many more sounds
you got in you?

05:00.267 --> 05:02.870
[ Clicking tongue ]

05:02.903 --> 05:03.837
Rrrr...

05:03.871 --> 05:04.838
The "Rrrrs" have it!

05:04.872 --> 05:06.039
You're taking care
of my brother.

05:06.073 --> 05:07.307
[ Exhales sharply ]

05:07.341 --> 05:09.343
Okay,
and what have we got here?

05:09.377 --> 05:12.380
That could be
an okay tablecloth.

05:12.413 --> 05:14.915
The funnel sort of looks like
a cornucopia.

05:14.948 --> 05:16.750
How's the glove turkey
coming?

05:16.784 --> 05:18.819
Do you really think
that looks like a turkey?

05:18.852 --> 05:20.988
I think it looks like
a son trying his best.

05:21.021 --> 05:21.922
[ Wheels rattling ]

05:21.955 --> 05:22.956
Oh, wait! Stop, stop!

05:22.990 --> 05:24.157
What is that?
Where is that going?

05:24.191 --> 05:26.059
I'm really not
supposed to say.

05:26.093 --> 05:27.928
You must be new here.

05:27.961 --> 05:30.030
This is Mom.

05:30.063 --> 05:31.565
You're about
to tell her everything.

05:31.599 --> 05:33.367
Great news.
I've saved Thanksgiving.

05:33.401 --> 05:35.503
I thought I knew
every corner of this hospital,

05:35.536 --> 05:37.170
but I've just learned
of this magical place

05:37.204 --> 05:39.039
where anything
is possible --

05:39.072 --> 05:41.041
the celebrity suite!

05:41.074 --> 05:42.510
I've heard the stories.

05:42.543 --> 05:43.544
They're real?

05:43.577 --> 05:45.679
Picture this --
satin sheets,

05:45.713 --> 05:47.381
ocean views,
butler on call.

05:47.415 --> 05:48.516
I mean, I don't know
if it has that,

05:48.549 --> 05:50.150
but if it's good enough
for Guy Fieri,

05:50.183 --> 05:51.251
it is good enough
for you lot.

05:51.284 --> 05:52.620
"Sounds amazing.

05:52.653 --> 05:53.687
You got it?"

05:53.721 --> 05:55.122
I did!

05:55.155 --> 05:56.924
I just got to go
and tell the hospital.

05:56.957 --> 05:58.659
Oh, come on!

05:58.692 --> 06:00.761
It'll be easy. Who else
are they gonna give it to?

06:00.794 --> 06:02.763
What other
special-needs supermom

06:02.796 --> 06:03.731
could possibly be here?

06:03.764 --> 06:06.900
**

06:06.934 --> 06:09.036
[ Gasps ]

06:09.069 --> 06:10.704
Melanie Hertzal.

06:11.338 --> 06:13.373
**

06:13.407 --> 06:14.842
L-O-- "Logan."

06:14.875 --> 06:15.709
**

06:15.743 --> 06:16.977
Jimmy:
Some rando I'm staring at

06:17.010 --> 06:19.647
because having an enemy
seems fun.

06:19.680 --> 06:21.148
Well, so long, DiMeos.

06:21.181 --> 06:22.683
I've got to go
save Thanksgiving.

06:22.716 --> 06:25.218
Oh, don't tell me you're trying
to get the celebrity suite.

06:25.252 --> 06:26.219
Oh,
I already got it.

06:26.253 --> 06:28.188
I just have to go
tell the hospital.

06:28.221 --> 06:35.963
**

06:37.230 --> 06:38.231
[ Bell dings ]

06:38.265 --> 06:39.099
You brought that?

06:39.132 --> 06:40.267
You didn't? Rookie.

06:40.300 --> 06:41.301
Nurse Stewart: Coming.

06:41.334 --> 06:42.269
Oh, please be someone
who loves me.

06:42.302 --> 06:43.336
Be someone
who loves me.

06:43.370 --> 06:44.337
Mrs. DiMeo!

06:44.371 --> 06:46.173
Silly.
They all love me.

06:46.206 --> 06:47.074
-And Melanie!
-Hi.

06:47.107 --> 06:49.076
First-name basis?
Easy, much?

06:49.109 --> 06:51.679
Stewart, sweetie,
I have a little favor.

06:51.712 --> 06:53.814
Me first.
I want the VIP suite.

06:53.847 --> 06:54.982
Oh...

06:55.015 --> 06:56.984
[ Clicking tongue ]

06:57.017 --> 06:58.218
Uh-huh.

06:58.251 --> 06:59.520
This boy's good.
Yeah.

07:02.222 --> 07:04.958
**

07:04.992 --> 07:09.329
"Great. Now we have to listen
to your dumb zingers all day."

07:10.297 --> 07:11.865
What's going on?

07:13.501 --> 07:16.336
"Complications
from tonsillectomy."

07:16.369 --> 07:17.571
He can't talk.

07:17.605 --> 07:19.973
He has to listen
to ou dumb zingers all day.

07:20.974 --> 07:23.577
"Finally, something
to be thankful for."

07:23.611 --> 07:25.579
Dad, this is great.

07:25.613 --> 07:27.414
If Logan's here,
Taylor's got to be here.

07:27.447 --> 07:29.416
I can finally get her back.
It's meant to be!

07:29.449 --> 07:31.485
Mm, hang on.

07:32.686 --> 07:33.621
Riding a horse?

07:33.654 --> 07:35.322
I -- uh -- A rowboat?

07:35.355 --> 07:36.857
Oarsman?
Skiing.

07:36.890 --> 07:39.660
Yes.
-Uh...a monkey skiing!

07:40.728 --> 07:42.329
Kissy face?
Boyfriend.

07:42.362 --> 07:45.799
Taylor is...
Both: On a ski trip
with her boyfriend!

07:45.833 --> 07:46.967
Yes!
Nice.

07:48.035 --> 07:50.003
Oh, hey, uh --

07:51.572 --> 07:53.340
I'm sorry. Neither of you
is getting the room.

07:53.373 --> 07:54.441
There's a guy ahead of you.

07:54.474 --> 07:56.009
So, you're saying
that if we could

07:56.043 --> 07:57.678
somehow get rid
of this person...

07:57.711 --> 07:59.179
I'm not saving that.
Let her finish.

07:59.212 --> 08:00.480
...that one of us
would then get the room?

08:00.514 --> 08:02.115
Should we bump
this guy off?

08:02.149 --> 08:03.884
Well, he's here,
and he's sick already.

08:03.917 --> 08:05.418
I meant off the list,
but that works.

08:05.452 --> 08:07.588
Eh, you know what?
I usually work alone.

08:07.621 --> 08:10.190
Well, so do I,
but desperate times...

08:10.223 --> 08:13.093
Okay, we work together,
get Famous Anus out of the room,

08:13.126 --> 08:14.261
and then we flip for it.

08:15.629 --> 08:17.464
Just please don't kill the guy
on my shift.

08:18.331 --> 08:20.133
Get ready to witness
a Thanksgiving miracle.

08:20.167 --> 08:21.969
I'm gonna get you
that room.

08:22.002 --> 08:23.904
Hey! I found out
who's in the suite.

08:23.937 --> 08:24.938
He's a big donor.
A hypochondriac.

08:24.972 --> 08:26.206
There's actually nothing wrong
with him.

08:26.239 --> 08:27.975
He just enjoys the attention
and the massage bed.

08:28.008 --> 08:30.578
Massage chair.
If I meant "chair," I would've
said "chair" -- "bed."

08:30.611 --> 08:33.080
Well, I'll get to him.
I have this whole place wired.

08:33.113 --> 08:35.015
The nurses love me,
the doctors fear me,

08:35.048 --> 08:36.516
and I buttered up
the weird morgue attendant

08:36.550 --> 08:38.251
because I wanted toe tags
for my luggage.

08:38.285 --> 08:39.352
Well, I've got
all the heating and A/C guys,

08:39.386 --> 08:40.520
and I'm tight
with the alarm tech

08:40.554 --> 08:42.089
'cause Logan's
a fire alarm-puller.

08:42.122 --> 08:43.323
Stop!

08:43.356 --> 08:45.458
Security lets me play
with their guns,

08:45.492 --> 08:46.459
and I've got
all the gossip

08:46.493 --> 08:47.928
on the desk-jockeys,
and they hate...

08:47.961 --> 08:49.763
Both:
Being called desk-jockeys.

08:49.797 --> 08:51.765
-Mm.
-Hey.

08:51.799 --> 08:54.134
Ohh, hey,
thanks for tagging along.

08:54.167 --> 08:56.469
Shopping's a lot more fun
when you got a backboard.

08:56.503 --> 08:57.805
Ah!

08:57.838 --> 08:58.772
Can't miss.

08:58.806 --> 08:59.973
What say
we wrap this up?

09:00.007 --> 09:01.441
Hey, what's the rule
with vegan stuff?

09:01.474 --> 09:04.211
Huh? It doesn't count
if you don't chew it?

09:04.244 --> 09:05.378
Right?

09:07.214 --> 09:08.215
Oh!

09:08.248 --> 09:09.783
[ Gulps ]

09:09.817 --> 09:10.818
You want anything?

09:10.851 --> 09:12.519
I want to unsee you
doing that.

09:12.552 --> 09:13.921
Hey, come on, man.

09:13.954 --> 09:15.789
Meat's got me
in a good mood.

09:15.823 --> 09:17.224
Let Uncle Billy treat you.

09:17.257 --> 09:18.425
Hey, hey!

09:18.458 --> 09:20.928
[ Quietly ] I'm a dentist.
I can write you a script.

09:20.961 --> 09:23.363
Oh! [ Whispering ] I have
a fun idea.

09:23.396 --> 09:24.865
You're crazy.

09:26.299 --> 09:27.334
What?

09:27.367 --> 09:29.202
[ Inhales sharply ]

09:29.236 --> 09:30.237
Ah!

09:30.270 --> 09:31.705
Sounds like
you're in pain, huh?

09:31.739 --> 09:32.706
Yeah.

09:32.740 --> 09:34.574
Same.

09:34.608 --> 09:37.110
Actually, not same,
because my pain is emotional,

09:37.144 --> 09:38.511
and there's no medicine
for that.

09:38.545 --> 09:41.314
What are you doing here?
You having a baby?

09:41.348 --> 09:43.516
Honestly, I thought I would
with Taylor,

09:43.550 --> 09:44.852
but she had other plans.

09:44.885 --> 09:46.119
After all the work
I put in

09:46.153 --> 09:47.655
to become a better man
for her.

09:47.688 --> 09:50.590
Pfft! There's 10 pushups a day
I'd like to have back.

09:50.624 --> 09:51.591
[ Exhales sharply ]

09:51.625 --> 09:52.626
I'll leave you alone.

09:52.660 --> 09:53.961
You seem like
you're ready to drop.

09:53.994 --> 09:55.663
Oh, no. Stay.

09:55.696 --> 09:58.231
I'm here alone,
and your story is helping.

09:58.265 --> 10:00.567
Really?
Yeah, it's so boring.
It's calming me down.

10:00.600 --> 10:02.836
Keep going.

10:02.870 --> 10:05.538
So, Taylor and I dated
for 10 months -- 10 1/2.

10:05.572 --> 10:08.541
We dated a little bit before
we became official-official.

10:08.575 --> 10:09.877
Let's just say 10 1/2,

10:09.910 --> 10:12.512
but if you put my hand
on a Bible, I might say 10.

10:12.545 --> 10:14.414
Were you friends first?

10:14.447 --> 10:15.382
Yes and no?

10:15.415 --> 10:16.684
That's perfect.

10:18.018 --> 10:19.386
Maya: Our mission --

10:19.419 --> 10:21.554
get the hypochondriac
out of the hospital.

10:21.588 --> 10:22.990
While I distract
Morgue Manny,

10:23.023 --> 10:24.524
who's desperate
to please me...

10:24.557 --> 10:26.593
Would you mind...?
Sliding you in a drawer

10:26.626 --> 10:28.095
so you can feel like
a dead person?

10:28.128 --> 10:29.396
Sure.

10:29.429 --> 10:31.932
Melanie: I get what we need
from the closet.

10:31.965 --> 10:34.101
We'll need a badge
to get upstairs.

10:34.134 --> 10:36.469
Luckily, on Thanksgiving,
people are working doubles,

10:36.503 --> 10:39.006
and somebody's going to be
taking a nap.

10:40.841 --> 10:43.276
I don't see why I have to be
the one under the cart.

10:43.310 --> 10:45.212
There's so many people
who know you.

10:45.245 --> 10:47.815
I mean, you are just
so...beloved.

10:47.848 --> 10:49.016
[ Crash ]
Ow!

10:49.049 --> 10:51.719
Well,
that was unavoidable.

10:51.752 --> 10:53.520
Nurse Michele's got
a weak stomach,

10:53.553 --> 10:55.923
but she's from Buffalo
and has never met a wing

10:55.956 --> 10:57.190
she didn't
have to weigh in on.

10:57.224 --> 10:58.792
[ Mouth full ]
Yeah, these are no good.

10:58.826 --> 11:00.560
Excuse me.

11:00.593 --> 11:03.764
**

11:03.797 --> 11:05.265
Shall we?

11:05.298 --> 11:07.300
Borrowed this
from my buddy in HVAC.

11:07.334 --> 11:10.503
Which leads us to
the most delicate step of all.

11:10.537 --> 11:11.538
Go, go, go!
Get out!

11:11.571 --> 11:13.273
[ Device beeping ]
The hospital is infested!

11:13.306 --> 11:15.308
-With what?
-DiMeo-Hertzal Disease!

11:15.342 --> 11:17.044
The readings
are off the chart!

11:17.077 --> 11:19.713
[ Quietly ] Bloody hell.
This place is fantastic.

11:19.747 --> 11:22.215
Aah! It's in my suit!
It's in my suit!

11:22.249 --> 11:23.717
Aah!!
Get it off me!

11:23.751 --> 11:24.752
Get it off!

11:24.785 --> 11:27.554
Don't worry.
It preys on relaxed muscles.

11:27.587 --> 11:28.789
As long
as you don't massage --

11:28.822 --> 11:30.057
I've had six!

11:30.090 --> 11:32.059
Have a very happy
Thanksgiving!

11:32.092 --> 11:33.593
Ha ha!

11:33.626 --> 11:34.928
Oh...

11:34.962 --> 11:36.096
Sauce!

11:36.129 --> 11:37.197
You had a wing.

11:37.230 --> 11:38.598
What?

11:40.067 --> 11:45.505
"There's an extra board
from a few years ago in my bag.

11:45.538 --> 11:48.341
Too bad
I enjoy your misery."

11:48.375 --> 11:51.644
**

11:51.678 --> 11:53.380
[ Sighs ]

11:53.413 --> 11:54.114
"Fine."

11:54.147 --> 11:56.016
There you go.

11:57.184 --> 11:58.285
[ As Borat ]
"I like."

11:58.318 --> 12:00.153
[ Normal voice ] Cool!
The Borat board!

12:00.187 --> 12:02.990
Not the Borat board.
So good.

12:03.023 --> 12:04.257
Well, I should go
check on Kenneth.

12:04.291 --> 12:05.725
No man
should have to endure

12:05.759 --> 12:07.494
my brother Billy alone
for that long.

12:07.527 --> 12:10.397
It's not
[as Borat] very nice!

12:10.430 --> 12:12.499
We'd finally moved on,
Jimmy.

12:12.532 --> 12:13.600
[ Chuckles ]

12:15.602 --> 12:20.240
"Thank you
for giving me a voice."

12:22.275 --> 12:24.912
"This board sucks.

12:24.945 --> 12:28.181
Your dad's Borat sucks.

12:28.215 --> 12:30.083
You suck."

12:31.251 --> 12:33.720
I wrote her a song.
It was really good.

12:33.753 --> 12:36.456
Kind of a, uh, "Paul Simon
meets Nickelback" vibe.

12:36.489 --> 12:37.791
-Huh.
-They're ready for you.

12:37.825 --> 12:40.293
Come with me.
-Oh, no. I-I need Ray.

12:40.327 --> 12:41.628
-Sorry, only family.
-Please?

12:41.661 --> 12:43.496
Ray, sing the song.

12:43.530 --> 12:44.564
Uh...

12:44.597 --> 12:46.699
* You're
the unforgettable pain *

12:46.733 --> 12:49.702
* You're the sweetest kind
of rain *

12:49.736 --> 12:52.172
-Really?
-* And my brain goes insane

12:52.205 --> 12:53.206
All right, come on.

12:53.240 --> 12:54.574
* When the Taylor train

12:54.607 --> 12:56.476
* Rolls through
my mainframe *

12:56.509 --> 12:58.611
[ Both laughing ]

12:58.645 --> 12:59.980
Feels funny.

13:00.013 --> 13:01.514
I thought
this was just for teeth.

13:01.548 --> 13:04.217
Oh, no. I'll let you in
on a little dentist secret.

13:04.251 --> 13:05.618
[ Quietly ]
It works everywhere!

13:05.652 --> 13:07.254
[ Laughs ]
Oh! Novocaine fight!

13:07.287 --> 13:07.855
Ah!

13:07.888 --> 13:11.024
[ Both laughing ]

13:11.058 --> 13:12.926
Guys?

13:12.960 --> 13:14.427
Are you...playing?

13:14.461 --> 13:16.563
Yeah!
This guy is great.

13:16.596 --> 13:18.598
I am digging
the "Billy Show."

13:18.631 --> 13:22.069
You guys are in the middle of
a hospital playing with drugs?

13:23.036 --> 13:24.771
I want in. Yeah!

13:24.804 --> 13:25.939
No, no.

13:25.973 --> 13:26.940
We're good.

13:26.974 --> 13:28.175
You do your thing.

13:28.208 --> 13:29.309
Kenneth, give the man
a thumbs up.

13:29.342 --> 13:30.677
[ Laughs ]

13:30.710 --> 13:31.711
I can't.

13:31.744 --> 13:32.846
He can't do it!

13:32.880 --> 13:34.014
[ Both laugh ]

13:34.047 --> 13:36.149
Hey, I'm gonna go see
how far I can get.

13:36.183 --> 13:37.184
I did my legs, too.

13:37.217 --> 13:37.951
Oh.

13:37.985 --> 13:41.054
[ Laughing ]

13:44.091 --> 13:45.258
Aww, Jimmy,
what's wrong?

13:45.292 --> 13:47.094
You're having fun.
You're getting Good Billy.

13:47.127 --> 13:48.962
I never get Good Billy.

13:48.996 --> 13:50.463
Jimmy, buddy.

13:53.967 --> 13:55.202
Put my arm on you.

13:55.235 --> 13:58.138
[ Sighs ]
Just enjoy.

13:58.171 --> 14:01.041
Well, we did it.
Thanksgiving is saved.

14:01.074 --> 14:04.945
I guess all that's left
is to flip for the room.

14:04.978 --> 14:07.047
I don't have a coin.
Nor do I.

14:07.080 --> 14:08.415
Hang on.

14:08.448 --> 14:09.917
Call it in midair.

14:09.950 --> 14:13.887
"Chiwetel" or "Theft of
this badge is a felony."

14:13.921 --> 14:14.922
Wait.

14:14.955 --> 14:17.024
What if we didn't flip
for it?

14:17.057 --> 14:19.659
What if we just went up there
and ate dinner all together?

14:19.692 --> 14:20.793
Oh, I don't know.

14:20.827 --> 14:22.595
O-Our boys really
don't get along.

14:22.629 --> 14:23.931
Wouldn't this be
an appropriate day

14:23.964 --> 14:25.966
to just put all that aside
and break bread?

14:25.999 --> 14:26.967
Yeah.

14:27.000 --> 14:28.535
I'll talk to JJ.

14:28.568 --> 14:30.437
Did we just
become friends?

14:30.470 --> 14:31.804
[ Inhales deeply ]

14:31.838 --> 14:32.839
God, I hope not.

14:32.872 --> 14:34.942
[ Chuckles ]

14:34.975 --> 14:37.177
Okay, Mary, one last push.

14:37.210 --> 14:38.378
[ Grunting ]

14:38.411 --> 14:40.313
And that's why
this world has nothing for me.

14:40.347 --> 14:41.748
Love is dead.

14:41.781 --> 14:43.816
I'm not being dramatic
when I say --
[ Baby crying ]

14:43.850 --> 14:47.154
life...has no meaning.
[ Baby crying ]

14:48.488 --> 14:50.223
Say hello.

14:50.257 --> 14:54.327
**

14:54.361 --> 14:58.031
Your name shall be Hope,

14:58.065 --> 15:00.233
for that is
what you have given me.

15:00.267 --> 15:02.669
And I will never
let you go.

15:04.972 --> 15:06.506
[ Breathing shakily ]

15:06.539 --> 15:08.675
I know
you don't like Logan,

15:08.708 --> 15:10.210
but I'm always
fighting for you alone,

15:10.243 --> 15:12.212
and we shared
this fight.

15:12.245 --> 15:15.748
I really think that
we should share the reward.

15:15.782 --> 15:18.051
"Don't trust these people.

15:18.085 --> 15:20.920
I trusted Logan
for a second,

15:20.954 --> 15:24.024
and he insulted
Dad's Borat."

15:24.057 --> 15:25.392
But Dad's Borat
is fantastic.

15:25.425 --> 15:27.194
"The room is empty.

15:27.227 --> 15:31.064
Did she really just
take Logan to the bathroom

15:31.098 --> 15:33.433
or are they taking it
right now?"

15:33.466 --> 15:35.868
Whose idea
was this truce?

15:35.902 --> 15:38.738
**

15:38.771 --> 15:41.008
Melanie Hertzal's.

15:42.342 --> 15:44.311
Melanie:
Open the door this instant!

15:44.344 --> 15:45.512
[ Singsong voice ]
Who is it?

15:48.815 --> 15:49.816
Oh.

15:50.917 --> 15:52.652
Hi, Ray.

15:52.685 --> 15:53.920
[ Softly ]
He just woke up.

15:53.953 --> 15:55.989
I just wanted to come say hi
to my little fighter.

15:56.023 --> 15:57.390
Well,
that's nice of you.

15:57.424 --> 15:59.659
He looks hungry.
Shall I give him some doughnut?

15:59.692 --> 16:02.162
Oh, I should nurse him

16:02.195 --> 16:03.730
and give him
some skin-to-skin contact.

16:03.763 --> 16:06.333
That's really important
for a newborn.

16:06.366 --> 16:09.202
I just feel so grateful
for him.

16:09.236 --> 16:11.538
And I want him to have the life
that I never got to have.

16:11.571 --> 16:12.905
Aren't you like 12?

16:13.773 --> 16:16.343
You'll be fine, Ray.
I promise.

16:17.110 --> 16:19.479
If you'd like to hold him
before you go, that's okay.

16:26.219 --> 16:27.520
Oh, I --

16:27.554 --> 16:29.556
I think it's working.

16:29.589 --> 16:31.424
[ Baby coos ]

16:31.458 --> 16:34.261
-Out.
-Hey, no need to push.

16:35.228 --> 16:36.263
[ Door locks ]

16:37.230 --> 16:38.065
What happened?!

16:38.098 --> 16:39.199
Do you have any idea

16:39.232 --> 16:40.733
what I had to do
to get those Buffalo wings?!

16:40.767 --> 16:42.735
You were gonna do the same
thing. I just did it first.

16:42.769 --> 16:44.271
Oh, you're wrong, Maya.

16:44.304 --> 16:47.207
I wasn't gonna screw you over,
but I am now.

16:48.941 --> 16:50.043
H-How's that massage bed?

16:50.077 --> 16:51.078
Not a bed!

16:51.111 --> 16:52.679
It is a chair
that reclines fully!

16:52.712 --> 16:55.182
It's r-r-r-r-really nice.
[ Chuckles ]

16:55.215 --> 16:57.517
Jimmy, wait up.

16:57.550 --> 16:58.851
Jimmy-y-y-y!

16:58.885 --> 17:01.854
I am sorry
I didn't hate your brother.

17:01.888 --> 17:04.124
And I hope
by phrasing it that way,

17:04.157 --> 17:05.658
you realize you're the one
that's being weird.

17:05.692 --> 17:07.060
It's not your fault.

17:07.094 --> 17:09.629
I just haven't enjoyed Billy
in forever.

17:09.662 --> 17:12.532
Why can't I get along with him
like I used to? I mean, you can.

17:12.565 --> 17:14.301
Well, it's easy for me.
He doesn't know me.

17:14.334 --> 17:16.136
You guys were close, huh?

17:16.169 --> 17:17.137
What kind of stuff
would you do?

17:17.170 --> 17:19.372
Oh, we'd bust on
the Bigelow twins,

17:19.406 --> 17:20.507
torture the babysitter.

17:20.540 --> 17:21.508
We were the worst.

17:21.541 --> 17:23.110
Well, see,
that's the problem.

17:23.143 --> 17:24.211
You're adults now.

17:24.244 --> 17:26.679
You need to connect
over adult stuff.

17:26.713 --> 17:27.714
Go deeper.

17:27.747 --> 17:28.515
I can help.

17:28.548 --> 17:29.849
[ Man speaking on P.A. ]

17:29.882 --> 17:32.585
Oh. No, you don't have to.
I see what you're trying to --

17:32.619 --> 17:34.087
Totally worth it.

17:34.121 --> 17:36.123
[ Exhales ]

17:36.156 --> 17:38.825
Are you supposed to be able
to see your breath in hospitals?

17:38.858 --> 17:40.660
She's got the A/C guy
in her pocket.

17:40.693 --> 17:41.661
[ Alarm blaring ]

17:41.694 --> 17:43.296
Oh!

17:43.330 --> 17:44.331
And the alarm guy!

17:44.364 --> 17:46.533
Thanksgiving in the bathroom!
Come on.

17:46.566 --> 17:49.001
Next year --
Chinese buffet.

17:49.035 --> 17:51.804
[ Softly ]
Today, I'm gonna help you two

17:51.838 --> 17:54.541
find a grownup connection.

17:54.574 --> 17:55.508
[ Softly ] Okay.

17:55.542 --> 17:56.443
Do we have to do it

17:56.476 --> 17:59.612
with soft, weird voices
like this?

17:59.646 --> 18:03.350
Billy, Kenneth's right. We've
never really talked about...

18:03.383 --> 18:05.252
[sighs] well, talked.

18:05.285 --> 18:07.086
[ Normal voice ] I'll start.

18:07.120 --> 18:08.155
Um, I'm Kenneth,

18:08.188 --> 18:10.423
and Kenneth
sometimes feels alone.

18:11.324 --> 18:13.893
[ Normal voice ]
I'm Billy, and, um,

18:13.926 --> 18:17.063
sometimes Kenneth tells
his problems to strangers.

18:17.096 --> 18:19.666
[ Stifled laugh ]
Okay, that's not
how this is really --

18:19.699 --> 18:21.901
I'm Jimmy,
and, uh, sometimes

18:21.934 --> 18:23.936
Kenneth starts an exercise
that backfires on him.

18:23.970 --> 18:25.272
[ Laughs ]
Wait, you, too?

18:25.305 --> 18:27.274
I'm Kenneth...
No, no, you're Billy.

18:27.307 --> 18:28.875
...and I bet you
I throw a football

18:28.908 --> 18:30.177
worse than
the Bigelow twins.

18:30.210 --> 18:31.311
Ha ha!

18:31.344 --> 18:32.412
I think this is working!

18:32.445 --> 18:33.846
Y-You're supposed
to go deep.

18:33.880 --> 18:35.615
Oh, okay,
okay, okay, okay, okay.

18:35.648 --> 18:37.984
[ Deep voice ]
I bet you I throw a football
worse than the Bigelow twins.

18:38.017 --> 18:39.319
That was totally it!

18:39.352 --> 18:40.287
[ Both laugh ]

18:40.320 --> 18:41.854
You guys
deserve each other.

18:41.888 --> 18:43.190
[ Both laugh ]

18:43.223 --> 18:44.757
[ Normal voice ]
Aww, come on!

18:45.525 --> 18:46.926
Jimmy: Hey, buddy.

18:46.959 --> 18:48.828
What's, uh, going on?

18:48.861 --> 18:50.863
I helped
deliver a baby today,

18:50.897 --> 18:54.734
held it in my arms,
fell in love,

18:54.767 --> 18:56.969
and then the mother banished me
from his life forever.

18:58.004 --> 18:59.839
Th-That happened today?

19:01.274 --> 19:03.910
You got a big heart,
Ray.

19:03.943 --> 19:06.313
No one's, like,
looking for you, right?

19:07.414 --> 19:09.649
A huge heart.

19:09.682 --> 19:12.051
And you let people in.

19:12.084 --> 19:15.288
That's not the way
for all the DiMeo men.

19:15.322 --> 19:17.657
The heartache's
gonna go away,

19:17.690 --> 19:18.725
but...

19:18.758 --> 19:20.627
don't lose that.

19:20.660 --> 19:22.929
[ High-pitched ]
Ooh, I'm Jimmy,

19:22.962 --> 19:27.500
and I have heart-to-hearts
with my son!

19:29.369 --> 19:31.304
I had that coming.

19:31.338 --> 19:32.739
[ Alarm blaring ]
Dinner's ready!

19:32.772 --> 19:35.408
Should we go around
and say what we're thankful for?

19:35.442 --> 19:37.444
[ Knock on door ]
Melanie: Cold enough?

19:37.477 --> 19:38.378
I'm just warming up.

19:38.411 --> 19:40.046
What more can you do?!

19:40.079 --> 19:42.081
[ Switch clicks,
blaring continues ]

19:42.114 --> 19:44.284
Okay, now what more?!

19:44.317 --> 19:45.918
Maybe we should just
give up the room.

19:45.952 --> 19:49.822
I wanted to save the day,
so I fought for it.

19:49.856 --> 19:51.991
But I don't know that
she was gonna take the room.

19:52.024 --> 19:54.427
Well, of course I was!
It's what we do.

19:54.461 --> 19:55.828
Well,
maybe we shouldn't.

19:55.862 --> 19:58.130
If families across America

19:58.164 --> 20:01.100
can get on with people
they loathe for one day a year,

20:01.133 --> 20:03.069
then, you know,
I think we can.

20:03.102 --> 20:04.136
You're right.

20:04.170 --> 20:06.739
[ Switch clicks,
blaring continues ]

20:06.773 --> 20:08.741
It's gonna take me a while
to turn off the alarm.

20:08.775 --> 20:10.176
Bugger.

20:10.209 --> 20:12.011
[ Bing Crosby's "I've Got Plenty
To Be Thankful For" plays ]

20:12.044 --> 20:13.413
[ As Borat ] My wife!

20:13.446 --> 20:17.317
* I've got plenty
to be thankful for *

20:19.286 --> 20:22.422
* I haven't got
a great big yacht *

20:22.455 --> 20:25.458
* To sail from shore to shore

20:25.492 --> 20:29.596
* Still, I've got plenty
to be thankful for *

20:29.629 --> 20:32.465
[ Sizzling ]

20:32.499 --> 20:40.139
**

20:40.172 --> 20:42.041
* Oh, I've got plenty...

20:42.074 --> 20:43.676
They need to be out
in five minutes.

20:43.710 --> 20:46.212
James Van Der Beek
sprained his toe.

20:46.245 --> 20:47.380
You tell 'em.

20:47.414 --> 20:49.982
**

20:52.785 --> 20:53.920
[ Babies crying ]

20:53.953 --> 20:55.121
Jimmy:
Time to say goodbye.

20:55.154 --> 20:57.690
It's the only way
you're gonna get closure.

20:57.724 --> 20:59.492
Hi, my little guy.

20:59.526 --> 21:01.961
Thank you so much
for showing me I can love again.

21:01.994 --> 21:05.131
I'll never forget
your little fingers

21:05.164 --> 21:06.499
and cute, little toes.

21:07.700 --> 21:08.868
I can't!

21:08.901 --> 21:10.703
You'll never understand
the connection I have

21:10.737 --> 21:12.271
with this child.

21:12.305 --> 21:13.306
Mary: Ray?

21:13.340 --> 21:20.112
**

21:20.146 --> 21:22.382
[ Baby crying ]

21:22.415 --> 21:24.717
Have a nice life, kid.
